# The bundled webview output is byte-for-byte what Vite produced.
# Source maps reference exact byte offsets and minified JS/CSS payloads
# carry trailing-newline + line-count semantics. Mark them binary so
# git stores + checks out verbatim across OSes — otherwise a Windows
# clone would get CRLF-normalised bundles that diverge from what the
# developer built and tested locally.
webview/** -text
